  [ lloydsmart ]
  * fix(ci): always kick off release after tagging; keep back-merge independent
  * fix(ci): include signed checksums in releases and ensure SHA256SUMS is generated
  * fix(ci): correct artifact upload syntax in _build.yml
  * fix(ci/release): lock release title to resolved tag to prevent “-1” drift

  [ Lloyd Smart ]
  * chore(release): prepare v0.2.13 [skip ci]

  [ lloydsmart ]
  * ci(release): force bash on steps that use bashisms (fix shopt error)
  * ci(build): enforce bash in reusable workflow to fix “shopt: not found”
  * ci(security): ignore RUSTSEC-2021-0154 (fuser) by default in cargo-audit
  * ci(uscan): handle uscan exit codes correctly; only fail on rc>=2

  [ Lloyd Smart ]
  * chore(release): prepare v0.2.14 [skip ci]

  [ lloydsmart ]
  * security: add policy-as-code for advisories + CI guard
  * ci(security): run cargo-audit only when Rust files change
  * cargo-deny: fix invalid TOML (remove db-path=null)
  * cargo-deny: update deny.toml to current schema
  * cargo-deny: allow Unicode-3.0 and quiet unused license warnings
  * deps: drop ANSI feature from tracing-subscriber to unify windows-* deps
  * cargo-deny: fix config key (unused-allowed-license) and keep Unicode-3.0 allow

  [ Lloyd Smart ]
  * Revert "Feature/security exceptions"

  [ lloydsmart ]
  * security: add policy-as-code for advisories + CI guard
  * ci(security): run cargo-audit only when Rust files change
  * cargo-deny: fix invalid TOML (remove db-path=null)
  * cargo-deny: update deny.toml to current schema
  * cargo-deny: allow Unicode-3.0 and quiet unused license warnings
  * deps: drop ANSI feature from tracing-subscriber to unify windows-* deps
  * cargo-deny: fix config key (unused-allowed-license) and keep Unicode-3.0 allow

  [ Lloyd Smart ]
  * chore(release): prepare v0.2.14 [skip ci]

