chd2iso-fuse (0.2.8-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  [ Lloyd Smart ]
  * Release v0.2.7

  [ lloydsmart ]
  * ci: run Bash for version check (fix [[ and BASH_REMATCH under sh)

  [ dependabot[bot] ]
  * chore(deps): bump actions/checkout from 4 to 5.
    Bumps [actions/checkout](https://github.com/actions/checkout) from 4 to 5.
    - [Release notes](https://github.com/actions/checkout/releases)
    - [Changelog](https://github.com/actions/checkout/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md)
    - [Commits](https://github.com/actions/checkout/compare/v4...v5)
    ---
    updated-dependencies:
    - dependency-name: actions/checkout
      dependency-version: '5'
      dependency-type: direct:production
      update-type: version-update:semver-major
    ...
    Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>

  [ dependabot[bot] ]
  * chore(deps): bump actions/github-script from 7 to 8.
    Bumps [actions/github-script](https://github.com/actions/github-script) from 7 to 8.
    - [Release notes](https://github.com/actions/github-script/releases)
    - [Commits](https://github.com/actions/github-script/compare/v7...v8)
    ---
    updated-dependencies:
    - dependency-name: actions/github-script
      dependency-version: '8'
      dependency-type: direct:production
      update-type: version-update:semver-major
    ...
    Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>

  [ dependabot[bot] ]
  * chore(deps): bump actions/download-artifact from 4 to 5.
    Bumps [actions/download-artifact](https://github.com/actions/download-artifact) from 4 to 5.
    - [Release notes](https://github.com/actions/download-artifact/releases)
    - [Commits](https://github.com/actions/download-artifact/compare/v4...v5)
    ---
    updated-dependencies:
    - dependency-name: actions/download-artifact
      dependency-version: '5'
      dependency-type: direct:production
      update-type: version-update:semver-major
    ...
    Signed-off-by: dependabot[bot] <support@github.com>
  * ci: removed old workflows
  * ci: add unified CI workflow for PRs and pushes
    - Run fmt, clippy, and tests on PRs (Linux)
    - Cache cargo registry/git for speed
    - Package Debian .deb artifacts on push to main/release branches
    - Skip runs for [skip ci] commits
  * ci: add release workflow triggered by tags
    - On tag v*, build and package using _build.yml
    - Verify versions with _verify-release.yml
    - Draft + publish GitHub Release with .deb artifacts and notes
    - Call reusable _release.yml for channel/APT (currently stubbed)
  * ci: auto-bump version and changelogs on release/* pushes
    - Derive version from branch name (release/* or hotfix/*)
    - Update Cargo.toml, debian/changelog, and release notes
    - Commit with [skip ci] to avoid workflow loops
    - Keeps release branches in sync before tagging
  * ci: rename release prep workflow to autobump.yml
    - Keeps file naming concise
    - Also enable on hotfix merges
  * ci: auto-create annotated tag on release/hotfix PR merge to main
    - Detect the merged PR for the push-to-main commit
    - Only proceed for release/* or hotfix/* source branches
    - Read version from Cargo.toml and verify via _verify-release.yml
    - Create and push annotated tag vX.Y.Z (no mutations to main)
  * ci: guard releases — only run when tag target is contained in main
  * ci: auto-open back-merge PR (main → develop) after release/hotfix merge
    - Trigger on push to main
    - Detect merged PR from release/* or hotfix/*
    - If develop is behind/diverged, open PR main → develop
    - No mutations to branches; conflicts handled in PR
  * ci: combine auto-tag and back-merge into single on-merge workflow
    - Trigger on push to main
    - Detect merged PR from release/* or hotfix/*
    - Verify versions via reusable _verify-release.yml
    - Create annotated tag vX.Y.Z (no mutations to main)
    - Open PR main → develop if develop is behind/diverged
    - Concurrency & [skip ci] guards included
  * docs: add developer runbook for release process
    - Document release and hotfix workflows (autobump, on-merge, release, nightly)
    - Provide TL;DR quick reference and detailed step-by-step guide
    - Include conventions, safeguards, manual overrides, and troubleshooting
  * fix(workflows): clean up release.yml to resolve YAML parse error
    - Removed stray/non-ASCII whitespace on `permissions: contents: write` line
    - Normalized indentation and ensured UTF-8 encoding
    - Replaced em dash in workflow name with a plain hyphen to avoid encoding issues
    This fixes the "Invalid workflow file" error reported on line 17 of
    `.github/workflows/release.yml` by GitHub Actions.
  * fix(workflows): repair merge.yml syntax and simplify outputs
    - Replaced non-ASCII arrow (→) with ASCII-safe `->` in step names and logs
    - Set outputs explicitly with `core.setOutput` instead of returning JSON
    - Updated conditions to read outputs directly (`steps.compare.outputs.status`, `steps.existing.outputs.exists`)
    - Ensures GitHub Actions parser accepts the workflow without YAML errors
    This resolves the "Invalid workflow file" error at line 120 in
    `.github/workflows/merge.yml`.
  * fix(workflows): sanitize merge.yml to resolve YAML parse error
    - Normalized indentation and whitespace (removed any stray tabs/non-ASCII)
    - Ensured only ASCII characters are used in step names and logs
    - Explicitly set step outputs with `core.setOutput` for clarity
    - Simplified `if:` conditions to read outputs directly
    This resolves the "Invalid workflow file" error reported at line 118 of
    `.github/workflows/merge.yml`.
  * fix(workflows): clean up merge.yml to resolve YAML parse error
    - Normalized indentation and spacing across all steps
    - Removed any potential hidden tabs or non-ASCII characters
    - Added explicit blank lines between steps for clarity
    - Ensured outputs are set with `core.setOutput` and conditions reference them directly
    This resolves the "Invalid workflow file" error flagged at line 117 of
    `.github/workflows/merge.yml`.
  * fix(workflows): harden merge.yml back-merge logic and resolve YAML error
    - Replaced inline complex `if:` expressions with a dedicated `gate` step
    - Added `should_backmerge` output to simplify conditions
    - Normalized spacing/indentation and ensured ASCII-only characters
    - Ensured outputs are set with `core.setOutput` for reliable parsing
    This change addresses repeated "Invalid workflow file" errors around the
    `Check for existing open PR` step in `.github/workflows/merge.yml`.
  * fix(workflows): quote job/step names in release.yml to resolve YAML error
    - Quoted all job and step names containing colons to avoid YAML parse issues
    - Removed non-ASCII symbols (emojis) for maximum portability
    - Normalized indentation and whitespace
    - No logic changes; only syntax/formatting adjustments
    This resolves the "Invalid workflow file" error flagged at line 17 of
    `.github/workflows/release.yml`.
  * fix(workflows): repair reusable build/verify workflows for merge/release
    - Removed duplicate `on:` blocks from `_verify-release.yml`
    - Added missing `nightly` input to `_build.yml` so conditions can reference it
    - Quoted workflow names consistently and normalized indentation
    - Aligned both files with proper `on: workflow_call` structure for reuse
    - Downgraded checkout action to `@v4` (current stable)
    These changes resolve the “invalid value workflow reference: no version specified”
    error when calling `_build.yml` and `_verify-release.yml` from merge/release workflows.
  * fix(workflows): pin reusable workflow calls in release/merge to branch ref
    - Updated release.yml to call reusables via
      lloydsmart/chd2iso-fuse/.github/workflows/*.yml@bugfix/release-workflow
    - Kept secrets inheritance and existing inputs (lane/nightly) intact
    - Quoted job/step names with colons for YAML safety
    This eliminates “invalid value workflow reference: no version specified”
    errors and ensures the caller resolves the correct reusable workflow versions.
  * fix(workflows): sanitize release.yml artifact/download block and pin reusables
    - Rewrote publish_release steps with clean two-space indents and ASCII-only chars
    - Ensured actions/download-artifact@v4 inputs (pattern, merge-multiple, path) are well-formed
    - Normalized all run scripts and simplified find usage
    - Continued to pin reusable workflow calls to @bugfix/release-workflow
    Fixes YAML parse errors around the “Download artifacts from build” step.
  * fix(workflows): sanitize release.yml around artifact download block
    - Simplified step names (removed colons/emojis), quoted artifact pattern
    - Reflowed block with ASCII-only, two-space indentation
    - Kept reusable workflow calls pinned to @bugfix/release-workflow
    - No behavioral changes; YAML-only hardening to appease the parser
  * fix(workflows): harden release.yml around artifact download block
    - Simplified and de-punctuated step names to avoid editor-introduced weird chars
    - Kept actions/download-artifact@v4 usage but ensured plain ASCII and clean indents
    - Normalized run scripts and paths in the publish_release job
    - Continued to pin reusable workflow calls to @bugfix/release-workflow
    Addresses YAML parse errors around the "Download artifacts from build" step.
  * fix(workflows): quote wildcard pattern in release.yml.
    YAML treats `*` as an alias, so the artifact download pattern must be quoted.
    - pattern: "chd2iso-fuse-*"
    This resolves the YAML parse error reported near the download-artifact step.
  * fix(workflows): make release.yml parser-proof and pin reusable refs
    - Expanded `needs:` to multi-line lists
    - Kept ASCII-only names and two-space indentation
    - Quoted the artifact wildcard pattern
    - Left pinned reusable workflow refs intact
    This addresses YAML syntax errors flagged around the artifact download step.
  * fix(workflows): simplify artifact download in release.yml to avoid YAML issues
    - Remove `pattern` from actions/download-artifact@v4 and download all artifacts
    - Keep clean ASCII, two-space indentation and simple step names
    - Leave reusable workflow refs pinned to @bugfix/release-workflow
    This addresses the YAML parse error reported around the artifact download step.
  * ci(workflows): another fix?
  * ci(workflows): force-normalize line endings, remove non-UTF8 bytes, replace tabs with spaces
  * debian/watch: switch to git refs backend for robustness.
    The previous watch file scraped GitHub tag pages for tarballs under
    `/archive/refs/tags/`, which is brittle and can break if GitHub changes
    its HTML layout or URL structure.
    Update to use the `mode=git` backend instead, so uscan inspects the
    remote git repository directly:
      * Match tags `vX.Y.Z` and `X.Y.Z` via `refs/tags/v?@ANY_VERSION@`.
      * Add `filenamemangle` to normalise tarball names to
        `chd2iso-fuse-$version.tar.gz`.
      * Add `dversionmangle` to strip epochs if ever present.
      * Use `debian uupdate` for smoother packaging updates.
    This makes `uscan` more reliable and future-proof while preserving
    expected orig.tar.gz naming.
  * ci: install gbp & Debian helpers for changelog step
    - Add git-buildpackage (gbp), devscripts, and python3-debian to runner
      so scripts/gen-debian-changelog.sh can run on CI.
    - Keep debhelper/fakeroot available (harmless here, useful if we build).
    - Echo tool versions for easier debugging.
  * ci(autobump): set DEBEMAIL/DEBFULLNAME for dch; keep gbp install
    - Export DEBEMAIL/DEBFULLNAME (and EMAIL) so gbp/dch can write debian/changelog.
    - Ensure git-buildpackage/devscripts/python3-debian installed on runner.
    - Leave git identity configured for the final commit.
  * ci(autobump): install git-cliff (with cargo fallback) and libdistro-info-perl
    - Ensure git-cliff is present for scripts/gen-release-notes.sh:
      * Prefer APT install; fall back to `cargo install` if needed and add cargo bin to PATH.
    - Add libdistro-info-perl to remove dch/gbp release-name warnings.
    - Keep git-buildpackage/devscripts/python3-debian in place.
    - Use Lloyd Smart <lloydsmart@users.noreply.github.com> for DEBEMAIL/DEBFULLNAME and git commit.

  [ Lloyd Smart ]
  * Release 0.2.8

 -- Lloyd Smart <lloydsmart@users.noreply.github.com>  Thu, 11 Sep 2025 09:56:00 +0000
=======
chd2iso-fuse (0.2.6-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  [ lloydsmart ]
  * ci(codeql): switch Rust to build-mode=none and drop manual build.
    Rust extractor doesn’t support manual build mode. Use build-mode=none and
    run the standard security-extended + security-and-quality queries.
    Removed the ‘observed’ cargo build (not used by Rust CodeQL).

  [ Lloyd Smart ]
  * chore(release): set Cargo version to 0.2.6 from tag
  * chore(release): sync Cargo.lock to version 0.2.6
  * Release 0.2.6

 -- Lloyd Smart <lloydsmart@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 07 Sep 2025 21:14:31 +0000
 
